					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">* Super Mario Brothers -- relies, somehow, on $FF being the default (World 0-1 vs. World 1-1) -- need more definitive info<br /></div><br />A common bootleg version of the ROM relies on RAM being initialized with $00, otherwise you start in world 0-1.  (You can still press A+Start to start in 1-1).<br />The real game doesn't care about uninitialized memory, although it does check for values in RAM to see if it has already booted or not.  (see Tennis swap trick)</div>

					
